# Line endings are governed HERE, not by core.autocrlf. .gitattributes overrides
# core.autocrlf, so every contributor gets identical bytes regardless of platform
# or local git config — set autocrlf to whatever you like, it no longer matters.
#
# Policy: git auto-detects text vs binary; every text file is stored AND checked
# out as LF — including on Windows working trees. dotcc builds and CI-runs on
# Linux, and a CRLF smudged into a bash script (`#!/usr/bin/env bash\r`) breaks
# it under WSL/CI. LF everywhere closes that whole class of bug.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Scripts execute on Linux / WSL / CI runners — pin LF explicitly (intent + belt).
*.sh  text eol=lf
*.py  text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf

# Committed .wasm probe fixtures (fable-wasm.md WF0) are the cached reference bytes —
# pin binary so no eol smudge can ever corrupt a blob (auto-detect would too; intent).
*.wasm binary
